'''Abu Jafar ibn Harun al-Turjali''' (died c. 1180) was born and raised in [[Trujillo, Cáceres|Trujillo]] to a noted [[Arab]] [[Muslim]] family. He received his education in [[Córdoba, Spain|Cordoba]] and later entered [[Almoravid]] service as a physician in [[Seville]] in [[Al-Andalus]], he was a talented reader regarding the works of [[philosophy]], he was thoroughly familiar with the Principles (''usul'') and the Branches (''fura'') of medical science, he was an excellent practitioner and his cures were frequently successful. He was the renowned educator of [[Ibn Bajjah]] and the young [[Ibn Rushd]] in his late years.<ref>{{cite book |url={{Google books |plainurl=yes |id=lKa9khFcKmQC |page=414 }} |title=Encyclopaedia of Islamic science and ...  |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2010-07-10}}</ref>

