'''Cathal Ó Matadain''', [[irish people|Irish]] [[philosopher]], died 1343.
Ó Matadain is described in the [[Annals of Lough Ce]] as ''a [[List of types of spiritual teachers|sage]] of [[Ireland]].'' In 1343, in unknown circumstances, he ''was killed by the Clann Ricairt'', or the Burke family of [[Clanricarde]] in what is now [[County Galway]].
