The '''Hussite Overture''' ({{lang-cs|Husitská, dramatická ouvertura}}), Op.&nbsp;67, B.&nbsp;132,<ref>{{cite web|title=Hussite Overture at the IMSLP|url=http://imslp.org/wiki/Hussite_Overture,_Op.67_(Dvo%C5%99%C3%A1k,_Anton%C3%ADn)}}</ref> was written by [[Antonín Dvořák]] in 1883 for the gala opening of the [[National Theatre (Prague)|Prague National Theater]].<ref>http://www.antonin-dvorak.cz/en/hussite-overture</ref> The composition was originally intended as a part of a dramatic trilogy on the Bohemian religious leader [[Jan Hus]].

The overture is scored for [[piccolo]], 2 [[western concert flute|flutes]], 2 [[oboe]]s, [[cor anglais]], 2 [[clarinet]]s, 2 [[bassoon]]s, 4 [[French horn|horns]], 2 [[trumpet]]s, 3 [[trombone]]s, [[tuba]], [[timpani]], percussion ([[bass drum]], [[cymbals]], [[triangle]]), [[harp]], and [[string section|strings]].

