{{Infobox person | name=Karel Verleye | image =| caption=[[Capuchin friar]], co-founder of the [[College of Europe]] and the [[Stichting Ryckevelde|Ryckevelde Foundation]] | birth_date={{birth date|df=yes|1920|4|17}} | birth_place=[[Mechelen]], [[Belgium]] | death_date={{death date and age|df=yes|2002|2|27|1920|4|17}} | death_place=[[Damme|Damme (Sijsele)]], [[Belgium]] }} '''Karel Verleye''' (17 April 1920 – 27 February 2002) co-founded the [[College of Europe]] in [[Bruges]] in 1949 with his good friend [[Hendrik Brugmans]].
He was a [[Capuchin friar]] for 64 years. In 1945 he became [[philosophy]] lector at the [[Bruges]] [[seminary]]. He founded the [[Stichting Ryckevelde|Ryckevelde Foundation]] in 1956.
