'''Paul Foulquié''' (16 March 1893 – 6 September 1983) was a French thinker and philosopher known for his books on [[metaphysics]], [[epistemology]], [[existentialism]] and [[psychology]].<ref>[http://www.idref.fr/026870649 Paul Foulquié]</ref><ref>[http://www.advaita-vedanta.co.uk/index.php/content/131-science-of-the-absolute-chapter-2-prologue Science of the Absolute]</ref><ref>[http://www.vqronline.org/articles/1994/winter/jones-sing-doo-wah/ Sing Doo Wah Diddy With Derrida] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929134748/http://www.vqronline.org/articles/1994/winter/jones-sing-doo-wah/ |date=2013-09-29 }}</ref> His works have been translated into different languages.<ref>[http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/mahdavi-yahya Yahya Mahdavi]</ref><ref>Existentialism, Paul Foulquie; Translated from the French by Kathleen Raine, Roy Publishers, Dennis Dobson, 1950</ref><ref>El Existencialismo (Spanish Edition), Paul Foulquie, Published 1998 by Oikos-Tau {{ISBN|978-84-281-0252-0}}</ref>
